'''The Sookie Stackhouse Companion''' is a book written by [[Charlaine Harris]]<ref>{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.co.in/books?id=asc6DxKmh8AC&source=gbs_navlinks_s|title=The Sookie Stackhouse Companion: A Complete Guide to the Sookie Stackhouse Series|last=Harris|first=Charlaine|date=2011-09-15|publisher=Orion|isbn=9780575097162|language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://charlaineharris.com/?p=154|title=The Sookie Stackhouse Companion|date=2011-08-30|work=Charlaine Harris|access-date=2017-03-27|language=en-US}}</ref> and published by [[Ace Hardcover]]/[[Ace Books]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.buffalolib.org/vufind/Record/1827478|title=Holdings: The Sookie Stackhouse companion /|website=www.buffalolib.org|language=en|access-date=2017-03-27}}</ref> (an imprint of [[Berkley Books]], owned by [[Penguin Random House]]<ref>{{Cite book|url=http://www.penguinrandomhouse.com/books/306255/the-sookie-stackhouse-companion-by-charlaine-harris/9781937007898/|title=The Sookie Stackhouse Companion {{!}} PenguinRandomHouse.com|language=en-US}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.barnesandnoble.com/w/sookie-stackhouse-companion-charlaine-harris/1100643472|title=The Sookie Stackhouse Companion|last=Noble|first=Barnes &|website=Barnes & Noble|language=en|access-date=2017-03-27}}</ref>) on 30 August 2011, which later went on to win the Anthony Award for Best Critical Non-Fiction in 2012.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.bouchercon.com/anthony-awards/winners-and-nominees/|title=Winners and Nominees|date=2015-08-10|work=Bouchercon|access-date=2017-03-27|language=en}}</ref>
