{{unreferenced|date=October 2018}} {{Infobox holiday | |holiday_name=Triumph of the Revolution (Triunfo de la Revoluci√≥n) |observedby=[[Cuba]] |scheduling=same day each year |date=January 1 |type=Historical |significance=Anniversary of 1958 revolution }} '''Triumph of the Revolution''' (Triunfo de la Revoluci√≥n) also known as "Dia de la Revoluci√≥n" is a celebration in [[Cuba]] of the anniversary of the victory of the [[Cuban Revolution|revolution]] led by [[Fidel Castro]] in 1959 which established the present government in Cuba. The previous president, Fulgencio Batista fled the country on December 31st, 1958. The holiday is celebrated on January 1st every year. ==See also== * [[Public holidays in Cuba]] * [[Cuban Revolution]]
